- "Recently resolved alarms" refers to alarms that have been resolved and the device is currently active;
- "Operational status" includes whether the device is active with an unresolved alarm, active with a resolved alarm, or without a recent alarm;
- Assuming each maintenance personnel is responsible for all devices, for simplicity.

- Alarm status 1 refers to an active alarm; 
- Alarm threshold is the minimum value that needs to be crossed to trigger an alarm;
- Location 1 refers to a specific location identifier.

; Alarm status = 1 refers to the device having triggered an alarm; 
; "Resolved" status indicates the alarm has been addressed by the responsible personnel; 
; Roles such as "building manager" and "maintenance personnel" imply different levels of responsibility and expertise in handling alarms and maintaining devices.

- "higher than the device's average" refers to the condition where a reading value is greater than the average reading value for each device; 
- A reading triggering an alarm implies that the reading value exceeded a certain threshold, which may vary depending on the device type; 
- Average reading value for each device is calculated based on all readings for that device.
